        <section class="segment-opener" data-uuid="f08f7f8d0c67455ca7e2123cc7c764f3">
            <article data-uuid="ad6fc79f2e674bd68e8ea7457f4f68db">
                <h4 data-uuid="6b02cf022b404164a5c10cc011065c4c">Main Idea</h4>
                <p class="main-idea" data-uuid="3497db01a3ac4b5c9ffc87d195e36078">The Industrial Revolution transformed life in the northern states.</p>
                <h2 data-uuid="46c11ad58014402782f7fe704fb25618">The Industrial North</h2>
                <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="f83a31ed79e447e5a956f64c5acef654"></div>
            </article>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="6a4e5d15fd11490fad91a9f079f6dd8e">As pioneers headed west, new industries grew in the Northeast. The first American factories used water-powered machines to make cloth. Inventor <dfn title="Whitney, Eli">Eli Whitney</dfn> later came up with the idea of interchangeable parts, which helped make mass production and less expensive goods possible.<br />
        </p>
        <section class="image-carousel" data-uuid="705800ce9d4a4688aba42122f3c89b5d">
            <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/image_carousel/index.html" data-uuid="e12c4da2c8b94187a9ceb0a5172217e5">
